name: Bruins
summary: In the NHL's Eastern Conference semifinals, the Bruins and Panthers have engaged in a heated rivalry. The Panthers took a 2-1 series lead with a 6-2 victory, scoring four power-play goals. In Game 3, the Panthers extended their lead to 3-2. However, Boston's captain Brad Marchand was scratched for Game 4. The Bruins' extra day off before Game 5 was seen as beneficial. The Panthers continued to dominate, winning Game 5 6-2. In Game 6, a disputed goal helped the Panthers clinch a 3-2 victory and take a 3-1 series lead.

name: Gayle King Sports Illustrated
summary: Gayle King, the renowned television personality, has made headlines by becoming the oldest woman to grace the cover of Sports Illustrated's Swimsuit Issue at the age of 69. King, known for her candid interviews and close friendship with Oprah Winfrey, expressed surprise and excitement about her cover debut, admitting that she had never viewed herself in that way. This historic moment has sparked widespread acclaim, with many commending King for challenging societal norms and showcasing the beauty and confidence of women of all ages. King has also shared that Winfrey was supportive of her decision to appear on the cover, further highlighting the power of female empowerment and the reshaping of societal perceptions of aging.

name: CPI
summary: Recent economic data suggests that inflation in the United States is easing. The Consumer Price Index (CPI) for April 2024 rose by 3.4% year-over-year, lower than the 3.6% increase in March. Domestic demand appears to be slowing, contributing to the decline in inflation. This has raised hopes that the Federal Reserve may consider cutting interest rates in 2024. Despite the positive CPI report, consumer prices are still rising at a significant 3.4% compared to last year. However, the market has reacted positively with a rise in stock prices as investors see the easing inflation as a sign of economic stability.

name: Assassin's Creed Shadows
summary: The upcoming Assassin's Creed Shadows is capturing attention with its intriguing premise. Set in feudal Japan, the game features dual protagonists - a samurai and a ninja - and boasts an ambitious open world. The first trailer showcases thrilling action sequences and highlights the game's blending of dual-character storytelling similar to Assassin's Creed Syndicate. However, fan reactions to the announcement of mini Battle Passes in this single-player game have been mixed. Despite this, Ubisoft has confirmed the game's release date as November 15th, and leaks have surfaced showcasing potential heroes. With its captivating setting and gameplay elements, Assassin's Creed Shadows seems poised to excite classic fans of the franchise.

summary: Jason Kelce, former Philadelphia Eagles center, has signed a multi-year contract with ESPN to join their "Monday Night Countdown" show. Kelce will bring his dynamic personality to the program. However, his recent comments suggesting that Triple Crown winner Secretariat used performance-enhancing drugs caused controversy. Kelce later apologized, stating he did not intend to spark outrage. Despite this, a mural honoring Kelce was unveiled at a Dunkin' store in Delaware County. Kelce's official role on "Monday Night Football" has now been revealed, and he will offer insights and analysis during the broadcasts.
